// This shader takes an already blurred image (uTexture) and uses a small, five-tap kernel to sample the image. The key feature is that the sampling kernel's position is jittered based on the uBlueNoise texture. This jittering slightly randomizes the final pixel color, which is essential for breaking up smooth blur patterns and creating the characteristic irregular texture of high-quality Bokeh.

